13/09/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Prosecution Office is investigating several people from Bugojno, Sarajevo and Gornja Maoca for suspected ties to the Wahhabi movement, prosecution spokesman Boris Grubesic told Glas Srpske on Monday (September 13th). They are suspected of terrorism and human trafficking. According to Grubesic, an investigation is also under way into several people arrested at the beginning of this year in Gornja Maoca, near Srebrenica, for illegal weapons possession. Glas Srpske cites sources who say that after the suspects were released from custody, they fled BiH, with some heading to Kosovo. (RTRS, Glas Srpske - 13/09/10)
